4.Run 
    
   perl maketrihed mktri.hed monophone1 triphone1


and edit mktri.hed

CL triphones1
TI T_l1_i {(*-l1_i+*,l1_i+*,*-l1_i).transP}
TI T_l1_u {(*-l1_u+*,l1_u+*,*-l1_u).transP}
TI T_l2_i {(*-l2_i+*,l2_i+*,*-l2_i).transP}
TI T_l2_u {(*-l2_u+*,l2_u+*,*-l2_u).transP}
TI T_l3_i {(*-l3_i+*,l3_i+*,*-l3_i).transP}
TI T_l3_u {(*-l3_u+*,l3_u+*,*-l3_u).transP}
TI T_l4_i {(*-l4_i+*,l4_i+*,*-l4_i).transP}
TI T_l4_u {(*-l4_u+*,l4_u+*,*-l4_u).transP}
TI T_l5_i {(*-l5_i+*,l5_i+*,*-l5_i).transP}
TI T_l5_u {(*-l5_u+*,l5_u+*,*-l5_u).transP}



5. Then create  3 more folders: hmm10-12 and execute the following commands

HHEd -A -D -T 1 -H hmm9/macros -H hmm9/hmmdefs -M hmm10 mktri.hed monophones1 

HERest  -A -D -T 1 -C config -I wintri.mlf -t 250.0 150.0 3000.0 -S train.scp -H hmm10/macros -H hmm10/hmmdefs -M hmm11 triphones1 

HERest  -A -D -T 1 -C config -I wintri.mlf -t 250.0 150.0 3000.0 -s stats -S train.scp -H hmm11/macros -H hmm11/hmmdefs -M hmm12 triphones1


6. Create a new HTK script file called maketriphones.ded containing the following:

AS sp
MP sil sil sp
TC

The TC edit command directs HDMan to output triphones.

Then execute the HDMan command against the entire lexicon file, not just the training dictionnary we have used thus far:

HDMan -A -D -T 1 -b sp -n fulllist0 -g maketriphones.ded -l flog dict-tri lexicon

This creates 2 files:

1. dict-tri
2. fulllist0


7. use 

   perl mkclscript.prl tree.hed triphones1 monophones1

and edit tree.hed

RO 100 stats

TR 0

QS  "R_NonBoundary"           { *+* }
