8. Next create  3 more folders: hmm13-15
Then execute the HHEd (hmm definition editor) command:

HHEd -A -D -T 1 -H hmm12/macros -H hmm12/hmmdefs -M hmm13 tree.hed triphones1 

HERest -A -D -T 1 -T 1 -C config -I wintri.mlf  -t 250.0 150.0 3000.0 -S train.scp -H hmm13/macros -H hmm13/hmmdefs -M hmm14 tiedlist

HERest -A -D -T 1 -T 1 -C config -I wintri.mlf  -t 250.0 150.0 3000.0 -S train.scp -H hmm14/macros -H hmm14/hmmdefs -M hmm15 tiedlist

9. Prepare test data:
Compute the Feature vector of test data same as training data.
	1. Create Codetest.scp
	    HCopy -A -D -T 1 -C wav_config -S Codetest.scp
	2. Create test.scp : Contains path to .mfc of test file.


10. Run the following command

HVite -A -D -T 1 -H hmm15/macros -H hmm15/hmmdefs -C config -S test.scp -l ’*’ -i recout.mlf -w wdnet -p 0.0 -s 5.0 t_dict tiedlist

To measure performance of the system.....
	create testref.mlf same as created word.mlf
		 perl prompts2mlf testref.mlf testprompt
	and run 
	HResults -I testref.mlf tiedlist recout.mlf


